rgeCrecoukias/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GeorgeCrecoukias/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GeorgeCrecoukias/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GeorgeCrecoukias/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GeorgeCrecoukias/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GeorgeCrecoukias/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GeorgeCrecoukias/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2012-09-27T01:40:17Z","updated_at":"2012-09-27T01:40:17Z","body":"Just starting to use this feature. I was surprised to see that the confirmation email is sent to the new email address. I was expecting to get an email at my old address to confirm the change. What if someone gets my password and changes the email to his/her address, then I don't even know what happened and my account is lost forever.\n\nTo summarize:\nChange email->send confirmation to old email->confirm->current email = unconfirmed_email->log user out->optional(get success email to your new email address)\n\nAm I totally misunderstanding what the feature is supposed to do? \n","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/heartcombo/devise/issues/comments/8915890/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"GeorgeCrecoukias","id":1043036,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwNDMwMzY=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1043036?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/GeorgeCrecoukias","html_url":"https://github.com/GeorgeCrecoukias","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GeorgeCrecoukias/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GeorgeCrecoukias/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/GeorgeCrecoukias/gists{/